From e2710927828a669fbe6965fab8da3dcc6d95acc1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Eric Koskinen <eric.koskinen@stevens.edu>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 11:37:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] Loop invariant support: syntax, checker, CLI stage, and
 benchmarks
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 1 — AST and syntax:
- ast.ml: While gains optional invariant field (exp node option)
- vcy_lexer.mll: new "invariant" keyword → INVARIANT token
- vcy_parser.mly: %inline while_inv rule; While stmt parses optional
  "invariant <exp>" clause between the guard and the body
- All traversals updated: interp.ml (interpret, infer_phis, verify_phis,
  cook_calls), ast_print.ml (source + debug printers), ast_to_c.ml,
  analyze.ml, spec_generator.ml

Phase 2 — invariants checker:
- src/vcy/invariants.ml (new): check_while_invariant verifies the
  inductive step {I ∧ G} B {I} by prepending assume(I∧G) and appending
  assert(I), then calling the existing assert-VCG infrastructure;
  check_block/check_stmt recurse through the AST threading accumulated
  type bindings; check_prog is the top-level entry point
- src/api/veracity.ml + veracity.mli: new check_invariants API function
- src/vcy/run.ml: new RunInvariants module and CmdInvariants CLI command
  ("./vcy invariants file.vcy --prover cvc5")

spec_generator fix:
- get_postconditions: skip variables in variable_ctr_list that are not
  in gstates (loop-internal vars like "steps", "tj", "nd" from the env
  block while loop were raising Not_found)

Benchmarks:
- benchmarks/invariants/: 10 new test programs covering ascending and
  descending counters, summation, doubling, tight bounds, two-variable
  ordering, stride-2 parity, accumulator, nested loops, and constant
  difference invariant — all verified by CVC5
- test.sh: new "benchmarks/invariants" section runs ./vcy invariants on
  each file expecting exit 0

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
